---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Editorial Standards"
  description="How BestKarma researches, validates, updates, and presents wellness content."
>
  <section class="bg-cream-dark/60 border-b border-border">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-6 py-16">
      <p class="text-sage-dark text-sm font-semibold uppercase tracking-widest mb-3">Editorial Standards</p>
      <h1 class="font-heading text-4xl md:text-5xl font-semibold text-bark">How BestKarma handles health content</h1>
      <p class="mt-6 max-w-3xl text-lg leading-relaxed text-stone">
        BestKarma aims to be practical, careful, and honest about uncertainty. The goal is to help readers understand what is well-supported, what looks promising, and what still deserves caution.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-6 py-16">
    <div class="grid gap-6 md:grid-cols-2">
      <div class="rounded-2xl border border-border bg-white/70 p-8">
        <h2 class="font-heading text-2xl font-semibold text-bark">Research standards</h2>
        <p class="mt-3 text-stone leading-relaxed">
          Articles should be grounded in primary research, high-quality reviews, and credible expert interpretation. Unsupported claims, miracle framing, and supplement hype should be rejected.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="rounded-2xl border border-border bg-white/70 p-8">
        <h2 class="font-heading text-2xl font-semibold text-bark">Validation workflow</h2>
        <p class="mt-3 text-stone leading-relaxed">
          Articles are reviewed before publication so they are clearer, better sourced, and more useful to readers.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="rounded-2xl border border-border bg-white/70 p-8">
        <h2 class="font-heading text-2xl font-semibold text-bark">Medical caution</h2>
        <p class="mt-3 text-stone leading-relaxed">
          BestKarma is educational media, not a medical practice. Content should avoid diagnosing readers, making treatment promises, or encouraging risky self-experimentation without appropriate caution.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="rounded-2xl border border-border bg-white/70 p-8">
        <h2 class="font-heading text-2xl font-semibold text-bark">Updates and corrections</h2>
        <p class="mt-3 text-stone leading-relaxed">
          Important corrections and major updates should be reflected on the article so readers can see when a piece was last reviewed or revised.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="mt-10 rounded-3xl bg-mist p-8 border border-sage-light/40">
        <h2 class="font-heading text-3xl font-semibold text-bark">What this means in practice</h2>
      <ul class="mt-4 space-y-3 text-stone leading-relaxed">
        <li>Every published article should include clear sourcing and basic review information.</li>
        <li>Confidence should match the quality of the evidence.</li>
        <li>When evidence is mixed, the article should say so directly.</li>
        <li>Content should privilege clarity and usefulness over sensationalism.</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
